# Unity Screenshot Automation

This guide provides C# patterns for taking automated screenshots in Unity projects. The examples use `ScreenCapture.CaptureScreenshot` and can be integrated into tests or editor scripts.

## Basic Screenshot Method
```csharp
using UnityEngine;

public static class ScreenshotUtil
{
    public static void Capture(string fileName)
    {
        ScreenCapture.CaptureScreenshot(fileName);
    }
}
```

## Capture During Play Mode Tests
```csharp
using UnityEngine.TestTools;
using NUnit.Framework;

public class ExampleTests
{
    [UnityTest]
    public IEnumerator CaptureScreenshot()
    {
        ScreenshotUtil.Capture("Test.png");
        yield return null; // wait a frame
        // Assert file exists or perform additional checks
    }
}
```

## Editor Script Example
```csharp
using UnityEditor;
using UnityEngine;

public class ScreenshotMenu
{
    [MenuItem("Tools/Capture Screenshot")]
    public static void Capture()
    {
        var path = "Screenshots/EditorScreenshot.png";
        ScreenshotUtil.Capture(path);
        Debug.Log($"Screenshot saved to {path}");
    }
}
```

Use these snippets as a starting point for automating screenshot capture within your Unity workflow.
